# Tool History + Anthropic: providerExecuted Workaround

## The bug (vercel/ai #11855, open as of March 2026)

When UIMessages with completed tool parts (state: 'output-available') are passed to `createAgentUIStreamResponse`, the SDK's `convertToModelMessages` creates:
- `role: 'assistant'` message with `tool-call` content
- `role: 'tool'` message with `tool-result` content

The Anthropic provider does NOT convert `role: 'tool'` messages to `role: 'user'` with `tool_result` content blocks. The Anthropic API rejects this with:

> "tool_use ids were found without tool_result blocks immediately after"

## Our fix (lib/chat/store.ts â†’ convertToModelUIMessages)

We set `providerExecuted = true` on all historical tool parts before passing them to the SDK. This makes `convertToModelMessages` inline both `tool-call` AND `tool-result` in the same assistant message, avoiding the separate `role: 'tool'` message entirely.

The Anthropic provider emits warnings ("provider executed tool call for tool X is not supported") but handles it correctly -- it strips the flag and sends normal tool_use + tool_result pairs.

## When to remove

When vercel/ai #11855 is fixed, remove the `raw.providerExecuted = true` line in `convertToModelUIMessages` and test that tool history still works with Anthropic.

## Tool naming: avoid Anthropic built-in names for custom tools

The Anthropic provider has special handling for tool names that match Anthropic's built-in tools (`web_search`, `code_execution`, `web_fetch`, `text_editor`). When `providerExecuted: true` is set and the tool name matches a built-in, the provider validates the output against the built-in tool's schema.

We use Anthropic's built-in `web_search` via `anthropic.tools.webSearch_20250305()` in `lib/ai/agent.ts`. If you add custom tools, NEVER name them `web_search`, `code_execution`, `web_fetch`, or `text_editor`.

## Do NOT

- Strip tool parts from message history (the old approach). The model needs cross-turn tool memory.
- Convert tool results to text summaries. That loses structured data.
- Use `type: 'tool-invocation'` with `state: 'result'`. That format doesn't exist in SDK v6. The correct format is `type: 'tool-${name}'` with `state: 'output-available'`, `input`, `output`, `toolCallId`.
- Name tools `web_search`, `code_execution`, `web_fetch`, or `text_editor` -- these collide with Anthropic built-ins when using `providerExecuted: true`.
